The article highlights the success of the author's plan to rebuild the American economy from the bottom up and the middle out. Since taking office, 7.4 million jobs have been created, providing families with stability. In February, 678,000 jobs were created, contributing to the overall growth and reducing the unemployment rate to 3.8 percent. Various industries, such as leisure and hospitality, construction, retail, and manufacturing, have seen job gains. Manufacturing and trucking jobs have particularly flourished, reaching the highest levels since 1994. The author attributes this progress to their economic approach and the successful management of the COVID-19 pandemic. Although rising costs remain a challenge, the United States is well-positioned to tackle the issue of inflation as it recovers from the pandemic.